      "subjectFrames": [
        "teachers_educators",
        "artists_makers",
        "communities_publics"
      ],
      "excerpt": "STUDIES in An Education A Journal of Issues and Research 26141, 247252 Copyright hy The National An Education Association Some Thoughts on Arts Education Frank Hodsoll The majority of students should have basic literacy in the major art forms by graduation from high school.",
      "quotes": [
        {
          "text": "Fourth, the conferences demonstrated widespread interest in the area of teacher education, and in the question of how better to prepare all kinds of teachers - classroom as well as specialist - to teach (or to teach about) the arts.",
          "tags": [
            "pedagogy",
            "teacherhood",
            "pedagogical_institutions",
            "teachers_educators"
          ],
          "families": [
            "perspectives",
            "signals",
            "locations",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Our young people need a sense of the past as well as of the present, and of a wider world than their own community, so that they can understand cultural expressions that go beyond their immediate surroundings and the ephemera of popular culture.",
          "tags": [
            "community",
            "situated_practice",
            "participation_relation",
            "relations_culture",
            "communities_publics"
          ],
          "families": [
            "perspectives",
            "definitions",
            "recognition",
            "locations",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Some degree of stan- dardization at the state level may be necessary, in terms of student testing (and perhaps in terms of teacher accreditation as well).",
          "tags": [
            "assessment",
            "pedagogy",
            "teacherhood",
            "testing_scoring",
            "pedagogical_institutions",
            "teachers_educators"
          ],
          "families": [
            "perspectives",
            "signals",
            "recognition",
            "locations",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "It seems to me that art is both creative and utilitarian, \"tenderhearted\" and \"hardheaded.\" The arts can be, and indeed are, vehicles for intellect as well as creativity and change.",
          "tags": [
            "creative",
            "cognitive",
            "creative_capacity",
            "mind_concepts"
          ],
          "families": [
            "types",
            "definitions",
            "locations"
          ]
        }
      ],
