      "subjectFrames": [
        "artists_makers",
        "teachers_educators"
      ],
      "excerpt": "STUDIES in Art Education A Journal of Issues and Research Volume 37, Issue 4 Summer 1996 Editorial Questions about Questions: Research in Art Education The new or renewed emphasis upon research within the National Art Education Association is a healthy sign for the field.",
      "quotes": [
        {
          "text": "It is a faith in reflective intelligence, an inheritance from the pragmatic tradition, which both inspires and requires the passionate commitment of those who plan, conduct, and disseminate research in art education.",
          "tags": [
            "language_reflection"
          ],
          "families": [
            "recognition"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "However, as some contemporary philosophers (MacIntyre, 1981; Rorty, 1979, 1982) have asserted for that field, we must avoid thinking that we have arrived at a foundational, perennial list of ques- 196 SALLY McRORIE tions or problems which undergirds art education.",
          "tags": [
            "cognitive",
            "philosophy",
            "mind_concepts"
          ],
          "families": [
            "types",
            "perspectives",
            "locations"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "The evolution of paradigm shifts is a holistic process that takes place his- torically both within and without, both \"subjectively\" and \"objectively.\" The research questions identified in the NAEA publications above are a good start in defining what currently needs to be known within the field.",
          "tags": [
            "community",
            "place",
            "place_ecology"
          ],
          "families": [
            "perspectives",
            "signals",
            "locations"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "It is a time of differing ideas about what art education should be, how best to pro- ceed in research and practice, just what constitutes excellence, and how it might be assessed.",
          "tags": [
            "making_performance",
            "artworks_materials"
          ],
          "families": [
            "recognition",
            "locations"
          ]
        }
      ],
