      "excerpt": "Copyright 2004 by the National Art EducationAssociation in Art Education AJournal of Issuesand Research 2004, 45(3), 189-205 Drawing on Experience: A Study ofVietnam Veteran Artists Karl F. Michel Western Carolina University This study is an exploration of the art produced by American veterans of the Vietnam War.",
      "quotes": [
        {
          "text": "It is also important to consider how the social milieu, namely the public lack of desire to deal with Vietnam, could have served to motivate these artists as well.",
          "tags": [
            "social",
            "situated_practice",
            "participation_relation",
            "artists_makers",
            "communities_publics"
          ],
          "families": [
            "types",
            "definitions",
            "recognition",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "The existence of the National Vietnam Veterans Art Museum in Chicago, Illinois made it possible to contact a national participant popu- lation.",
          "tags": [
            "community",
            "museum",
            "participation_relation",
            "communities_publics"
          ],
          "families": [
            "perspectives",
            "signals",
            "recognition",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "In the areas of artistic history, military service, and the creative process, Vietnam veteran artists are a diverse group, and there are many different ways of explaining the connection between Vietnam experience and their art.",
          "tags": [
            "creative",
            "creative_capacity",
            "artists_makers"
          ],
          "families": [
            "types",
            "definitions",
            "subjects"
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "In this way, Vietnam experience was a potential catalyst for defining one's identity and for establishing priorities in life.",
          "tags": [
            "social",
            "identity",
            "situated_practice"
          ],
          "families": [
            "types",
            "signals",
            "definitions"
          ]
        }
      ],
